notesStmt.note: Some poetical pieces appended on the end-flyleaves, on folio 1v and 164r.
Musa ibn Yaḥya Al-Sari: inscribed, folio 2r, 163v.
Manuscript description based on Margoliouth, G.: Catalogue of the Hebrew and Samaritan Manuscripts in the British Museum, London 1965.

msContents.summary: Midrash ha-gadol on Numbers, attributed to David Adani.

layoutDesc.layout: Columns: 1; ruled lines: 28; written lines: 28; Marginal notes and additions. Hard-point ruling visible.

scriptDesc.scriptNote: Yemenite semi-cursive script of the 15th century.

binding.p: BM/BL in-house. Spine title: 'Midrash Haggadol. Numbers. Hebrew. Brit. Mus. Oriental 2215.'

history.provenance: Acquisition: Moses Wilhelm Shapira (b. 1830, d. 1884), an antiquities dealer of Jerusalem: purchased by the British Library from him on 13 December 1879, inscribed, folio [168v].
